        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "@zeertzjq using `fnameescape()` does **not** fix this issue on windows, because `(` and `)` are not part of `isfname`. There are a lot of plugins that still have issues with this to this day (just look at the mentions in #24542). If we can't include a fix for this in neovim, I think we should at least provide a recommended fix. Can you help with this?\n\nI found that [nvim-tree/nvim-tree.lua](https://github.com/nvim-tree/nvim-tree.lua) fixed this on their own in https://github.com/nvim-tree/nvim-tree.lua/pull/2374 using a helper function in addition to `fnameescape()` (thanks @davisthedev):\n\n```lua\n-- Escapes special characters in string if windows else returns unmodified string.\n-- @param path string\n-- @return path\nfunction M.escape_special_chars(path)\n  if path == nil then\n    return path\n  end\n  return M.is_windows and path:gsub(\"%(\", \"\\\\(\"):gsub(\"%)\", \"\\\\)\") or path\nend\n```\n",
