        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "To be clear: I am not a maintainer of either of the plugins, just an invested user.\n\n### How nvim-tree.lua opens files:\nhttps://github.com/nvim-tree/nvim-tree.lua/blob/8e8be709c9a93e1ebefde7964884a8b564bfd3e0/lua/nvim-tree/actions/node/open-file.lua#L168-L184\n\nBut they fixed it by doing this:\nhttps://github.com/nvim-tree/nvim-tree.lua/blob/8e8be709c9a93e1ebefde7964884a8b564bfd3e0/lua/nvim-tree/utils.lua#L50-L65\n\n### How telescope.nvim opens files:\nhttps://github.com/nvim-telescope/telescope.nvim/blob/9377230aa5305d9e9aca4ed8dadf1070fb4aa9fc/lua/telescope/actions/set.lua#L100\n\nTelescope is still unable to open files with `(` in path, **only on WINDOWS**.\n\nSo what's the final recommendation here? using `bufadd()` / `bufload()`?\n\nEdit: idk why github isn't displaying the code inline...\n",
