        "author_association": "MEMBER",
        "body": "@lmgraf how are you opening the file?\n\nThis may be another case where `:nospecial` https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/37862 would be helpful.\n\nWe could try adding parens to 'isfname' (affects `gf`), but maybe not be necessary; `bufadd()` / `bufload()` seem to reliably avoid filename special chars and 'isfname':\n\n    :call nvim_win_set_buf(0, bufadd('app/(login)/_layout.tsx'))\n    :setlocal buflisted\n\nI'll document that somewhere, unless someone knows better...",
